14/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Anti-terror police announced on Monday (March 14th) they have seized weapons caches and arrested seven people in operations in the central town of Volos and in Athens.
An assortment of weapons and disguises were found as well.
The detained, five men and two women, will be questioned.
In other news, a bomb exploded early Monday in the office of the ruling PASOK party in Thessaloniki's district of Sykies.
The fire that followed caused damage but no injuries.
(ANA-MPA, ERT, Eleftherotypia, To Vima - 14/03/11)
